    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/10–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 20, 1954—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 54. Re: Non-Member Participation <gloss
                        target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> [<gloss target="#t_UN1">
                        <hi rend="italic">UN</hi>
                    </gloss>]. Secretary has decided we should let our non-member participation
                    proposal “coast”. He expressed views (1) useful for US to have formulated idea
                    and brought it to attention other delegations; and (2) if idea seeps <pb
                        facs="1083" n="1055" xml:id="pg_1055"/> in for year may bear fruit next
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Secretary also suggested <gloss
                        target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> should make clear to others our belief
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> bound to wither away unless it becomes
                    more universal.</p>
                <p>In further membership discussions <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> should
                    act on above basis. Department will send separate instructions re Japan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
